A nice atmosphere bar. Our server/bar tender was Charlie and he did great while single handedly managing about 15 people at a time between bar, and tables. He checked on us pretty often but wasn‚Äôt overly pushy.
We ordered a couple beers and a chicken bacon ranch pan pizza. Pretty good pizza. Not the best I ever had but I‚Äôd order it again.
A bit disappointing that the beer menu didn‚Äôt match the list of beers on draft but happy with lots of choices.

The server Sophie assured me the pizza would take 10-15 minutes since I only came in for a take out order. Over 45 minutes after ordering I ask her about it and she says ‚Äòit looks like it‚Äôs ready and they‚Äôre cutting it up right now‚Äô. Then she leaves and continues to prioritize the other tables while ignoring the 5 people at the bar. It‚Äôs now been an hour and she started to avoid the left side of the bar.

I‚Äôm upset and this sucks because service here on a different night was great with the server Laura(?). She actually answered the phone was attentive.

*Finally got my pizza with an apology, and it is barely even warm.

detailedReviews.author: Noah Hanmer
detailedReviews.text: While I customarily do not write Google reviews, the service was so excellent I couldn't pass up the opportunity to do so. I came to Dan Kelly's anticipating, and ultimately getting, a party of about thirty people joining me. Considering that staff had no warning that this level of intensity was coming to the establishment, they, and especially Laurel, did a fantastic job of managing sporadic orders, making sure the correct people got the correct orders, keeping track of the exact items, and ensuring no detail was forgotten. I cannot recommend them enough, and Laurel deserves a Nobel Prize for keeping up with the insanity. Oh yeah, and the food was delicious, even as cold leftovers. Thanks, Dan Kelly's!

detailedReviews.author: D Kingston
detailedReviews.text: Stopped in briefly on a weekday night,  as we heard there were thc beverages available. Didn't get to try the food,  but have heard good things about their pizza.  Only qualm is this: the place was busy but not insane from the service industry worker point of view.  The bar seats were not full and there were a handful of tables open, for example.  There were 3 bartenders behind the bar,  and we waited for 10-15 minutes for a thc drink and 2 of the special shots that were highlighted on the chalkboard above the bar.  With 3 bartenders,  space at the bar itself,  open tables  and we wait 10-15 minutes? Get your staff up to snuff and teach them to hustle a bit more. More money for the business and more money for them! Thanks! PS- love the secret peephole. Lol. Also,  yay pulltabs!

detailedReviews.author: Richard Voytas
detailedReviews.text: This was the worst pizza experience and an incredibly poor example of customer service.  At about 4:30pm, I placed an order in advance for $80 worth of pizza and wings to be delivered at 6:15.  By 7:15, nobody had delivered any pizza and nobody called me.  I called the business.  They told me that they "messed up" the order and would not deliver any pizza.  I asked for a refund.  They said no.  I asked to talk to a manager, who told me I could get gift cards but no refund.  I paid the $80.  They kept it.  They did not deliver any pizza.  My credit card company did end up reversing the charges when I called in to report the fraud. Stay away from this business.  These are bad human beings.
